                "text": "{\"answer\":\"The most relevant bibliographic production by Alba Cristina Magalhães Alves de Melo in 2024 includes:\\n\\n*   **\"The Megapixel Approach for Efficient Execution of Irregular Wavefront Algorithms on GPUs\"**: Published in IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON PARALLEL AND DISTRIBUTED SYSTEMS, this paper focuses on efficiently executing irregular wavefront algorithms on GPUs.\\n*   **\"MAS-Cloud+: A novel multi-agent architecture with reasoning models for resource management in multiple providers\"**: Published in Future Generation Computer Systems, this work introduces a multi-agent architecture for resource management across multiple cloud providers.\\n*   **\"A novel GPU-based approach for embedded NARMAX/FROLS system identification\"**: Published in MECHANICAL SYSTEMS AND SIGNAL PROCESSING, this paper presents a GPU-based method for system identification.\\n*   **\"Adaptive Patch Grid Strategy for Parallel Protein Folding using Atomic Burials with NAMD\"**: Published in JOURNAL OF PARALLEL AND DISTRIBUTED COMPUTING, this research focuses on an adaptive strategy for parallel protein folding simulation.\\n*   **\"A Framework for Automated Parallel Execution of Scientific Multi-workflow Applications in the Cloud with Work Stealing\"**: Published in Euro-Par, this work details a framework for parallel execution of scientific workflows in the cloud.\",\"most_relevant_production\": \"The most relevant bibliographic productions in 2024 are: \\\"The Megapixel Approach for Efficient Execution of Irregular Wavefront Algorithms on GPUs\\\" published in IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON PARALLEL AND DISTRIBUTED SYSTEMS, \\\"MAS-Cloud+: A novel multi-agent architecture with reasoning models for resource management in multiple providers\\\" published in Future Generation Computer Systems, \\\"A novel GPU-based approach for embedded NARMAX/FROLS system identification\\\" published in MECHANICAL SYSTEMS AND SIGNAL PROCESSING, \\\"Adaptive Patch Grid Strategy for Paralle